description: HfSiTe crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HfSiTe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hf(1) is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Si(1) and four equivalent Te(1) atoms. All Hf(1)-Si(1) bond lengths are 2.793 Å. All Hf(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.945 Å. Si(1) is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Hf(1) and four equivalent Si(1) atoms. All Si(1)-Si(1) bond lengths are 2.593 Å. Te(1) is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Hf(1) atoms.

As crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmna space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of two As clusters. As(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one As(1) atom. The As(1)-As(1) bond length is 2.504 Å.

TiOBr crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiOBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ti(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing TiBr₂O₄ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 6°. There are two shorter (2.024 Å) and two longer (2.063 Å) Ti(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Both Ti(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.587 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent Ti(1)³⁺ atoms. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ti(1)³⁺ atoms.

InBi crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one InBi sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In(1) is bonded to four equivalent Bi(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing InBi₄ tetrahedra. All In(1)-Bi(1) bond lengths are 3.068 Å. Bi(1) is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent In(1) atoms.

NbO₂ is Molybdenite-like structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P̅6m2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NbO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Nb(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.101 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

SbAsO₃ crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SbAsO₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one O(2)²⁻, one O(3)²⁻, and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. The Sb(1,2)-O(2) bond length is 2.036 Å. The Sb(1,2)-O(3) bond length is 2.011 Å. There is one shorter (2.058 Å) and one longer (2.638 Å) Sb(1,2)-O(1) bond length. As(1,2)¹⁺ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to one O(1)²⁻ and one O(4)²⁻ atom. The As(1,2)-O(1) bond length is 1.825 Å. The As(1,2)-O(4) bond length is 1.825 Å. There are six inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ and one As(1,2)¹⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ atom. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ and one As(1,2)¹⁺ atom. The O(3)-As(1,2) bond length is 1.825 Å. In the fourth O²⁻ site, O(4)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ and one As(1,2)¹⁺ atom. The O(4)-Sb(1,2) bond length is 2.011 Å. In the fifth O²⁻ site, O(5)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ and one As(1,2)¹⁺ atom. There is one shorter (2.058 Å) and one longer (2.638 Å) O(5)-Sb(1,2) bond length. The O(5)-As(1,2) bond length is 1.826 Å. In the sixth O²⁻ site, O(6)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Sb(1,2)⁵⁺ atom. The O(6)-Sb(1,2) bond length is 2.036 Å.

MoO₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one MoO₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Mo(1)⁶⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to one O(1)²⁻, two equivalent O(3)²⁻, and three equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. The Mo(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.675 Å. There is one shorter (1.767 Å) and one longer (2.156 Å) Mo(1)-O(3) bond length. There are two shorter (1.946 Å) and one longer (2.441 Å) Mo(1)-O(2) bond length. There are three inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Mo(1)⁶⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Mo(1)⁶⁺ atoms. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent Mo(1)⁶⁺ atoms.

CrGeTe₃ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅31m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CrGeTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cr(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CrTe₆ octahedra. All Cr(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.779 Å. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. All Ge(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.630 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Cr(1)²⁺ and one Ge(1)⁴⁺ atom.

ZrNBr crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ZrNBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are three shorter (2.158 Å) and one longer (2.180 Å) Zr(1)-N(1) bond length. All Zr(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.897 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NZr₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

PdSeO₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of one PdSeO₃ ribbon oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. Pd(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. Both Pd(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.038 Å. Both Pd(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.023 Å. Se(1)²⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one O(2)²⁻ atom. The Se(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.844 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Pd(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Pd(1)⁴⁺ and one Se(1)²⁺ atom.

NbOBr₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmm2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NbOBr₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻, two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻, and two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing NbBr₄O₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 3°. There is one shorter (1.865 Å) and one longer (2.060 Å) Nb(1)-O(1) bond length. Both Nb(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.609 Å. Both Nb(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 2.695 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)⁴⁺ atoms. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

SrSbSe₂F crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SrSbSe₂F sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Se(2)²⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Sr(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 3.183 Å. All Sr(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.508 Å. Sb(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one Se(2)²⁻ and four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. The Sb(1)-Se(2) bond length is 2.546 Å. All Sb(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.928 Å. There are two inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and one Sb(1)³⁺ atom. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FSr₄ tetrahedra.

Lix₀CoO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoO₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.876 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

AgI crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AgI sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ag(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.917 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms.

CoI₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CoI₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoI₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.741 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Co(1)²⁺ atoms.

NbSe₂Br₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NbSe₂Br₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)+4.50+ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)²⁻, two equivalent Se(2)²⁻, and four equivalent Br(1)+0.25- atoms. Both Nb(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.642 Å. Both Nb(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 2.660 Å. There are two shorter (2.772 Å) and two longer (2.790 Å) Nb(1)-Br(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)+4.50+ atoms. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)+4.50+ atoms. Br(1)+0.25- is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)+4.50+ atoms.

ZrNBr crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ZrNBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.151 Å) and two longer (2.160 Å) Zr(1)-N(1) bond lengths. Both Zr(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.768 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing NZr₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

InBr₃ is Chromium trichloride-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one InBr₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1,2)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing InBr₆ octahedra. All In(1)-Br(1,2) bond lengths are 2.716 Å. Br(1,2)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms.

YI(Ga) crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YI(Ga) sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Y(1) is bonded to six equivalent Ga(1) and three equivalent I(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing YGa₆I₃ octahedra. There are three shorter (2.931 Å) and three longer (3.382 Å) Y(1)-Ga(1) bond lengths. All Y(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.132 Å. Ga(1) is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Y(1) and three equivalent Ga(1) atoms. All Ga(1)-Ga(1) bond lengths are 2.515 Å. I(1) is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Y(1) atoms.

YI₃ is Bismuth triodide-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅31m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YI₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing YI₆ octahedra. All Y(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.030 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms.

NbCoTe₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NbCoTe₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(2)²⁻ and three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.827 Å) and one longer (2.891 Å) Nb(1)-Te(2) bond length. There are a spread of Nb(1)-Te(1) bond distances ranging from 2.829-3.007 Å. Co(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.616 Å) and one longer (2.663 Å) Co(1)-Te(1) bond length. There is one shorter (2.550 Å) and one longer (2.589 Å) Co(1)-Te(2) bond length. There are two inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Co(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Co(1)²⁺ atoms.

MnSe crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one MnSe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Mn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing MnSe₄ tetrahedra. All Mn(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.382 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Mn(1)²⁺ atoms.

AlOOH crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AlOOH sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing AlO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 23°. Both Al(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.902 Å. There are two shorter (1.891 Å) and two longer (1.951 Å) Al(1)-O(2) bond lengths. H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one O(1)²⁻ atom. The H(1)-O(1) bond length is 0.965 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Al(1)³⁺ and one H(1)¹⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OAl₄ trigonal pyramids.

Lix₀CoO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoO₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.876 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

BiBr₃ is Bismuth triodide-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one BiBr₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1,2,3)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing BiBr₆ octahedra. All Bi(1)-Br(1,2,3) bond lengths are 2.896 Å. Br(1,2,3)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms.

YOBr crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YOBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.285 Å) and three longer (2.286 Å) Y(1)-O(1) bond lengths. All Y(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.933 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OY₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms.

Mg(ReO₄)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Mg(ReO₄)₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form MgO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Re(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All Mg(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.072 Å. Re(1)⁷⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻ and three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form ReO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Mg(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 21°. The Re(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.724 Å. All Re(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.760 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 150 degrees geometry to one Mg(1)²⁺ and one Re(1)⁷⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Re(1)⁷⁺ atom.

BiOF crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one BiOF sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.248 Å) and three longer (2.405 Å) Bi(1)-O(1) bond lengths. All Bi(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.490 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OBi₄ tetrahedra. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms.

NiTeO₄ is trigonal omega-derived structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NiTeO₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ni(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form NiO₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Ni(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Ni(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.123 Å. All Ni(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.053 Å. Te(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form TeO₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Ni(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Te(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.918 Å. All Te(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.051 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Ni(1)⁴⁺ and one Te(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Ni(1)⁴⁺ and two equivalent Te(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

TiZrTe₄ is trigonal omega-derived structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiZrTe₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and four equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms to form ZrTe₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Zr(1)Te₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Ti(1)Te₆ octahedra. Both Zr(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.889 Å. All Zr(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 2.896 Å. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Te(2)²⁻ and four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form TiTe₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Ti(1)Te₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Zr(1)Te₆ octahedra. Both Ti(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 2.816 Å. All Ti(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.804 Å. There are two inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Zr(1)⁴⁺ and two equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ and one Ti(1)⁴⁺ atom.

Si₃H crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Si₃H sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are three inequivalent Si sites. In the first Si site, Si(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to three equivalent Si(2) and one H(1) atom. All Si(1)-Si(2) bond lengths are 2.366 Å. The Si(1)-H(1) bond length is 1.510 Å. In the second Si site, Si(2) is bonded to one Si(3) and three equivalent Si(1) atoms to form corner-sharing SiSi₄ tetrahedra. The Si(2)-Si(3) bond length is 2.391 Å. In the third Si site, Si(3) is bonded to one Si(2) and three equivalent Si(3) atoms to form corner-sharing SiSi₄ tetrahedra. All Si(3)-Si(3) bond lengths are 2.378 Å. H(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Si(1) atom.

Lix₀CoO₂ is Cyanogen Chloride-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ cluster. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.586 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Co(1)⁴⁺ atom.

VO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one VO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. V(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing VO₆ octahedra. All V(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.944 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent V(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

TeO₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P̅6m2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TeO₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Te(1)⁶⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing TeO₅ trigonal bipyramids. Both Te(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.797 Å. All Te(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.170 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Te(1)⁶⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Te(1)⁶⁺ atoms.

BiO₂ crystallizes in the hexagonal P̅6m2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one BiO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1) atoms. All Bi(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.396 Å. O(1) is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Bi(1) atoms.

Ho₂C is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ho₂C sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ho(1) is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent C(1) atoms. All Ho(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 2.427 Å. C(1) is bonded to six equivalent Ho(1) atoms to form edge-sharing CHo₆ octahedra.

Zr₂PTe₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Zr₂PTe₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. YCBr crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YCBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two shorter (2.882 Å) and one longer (3.033 Å) Y(1)-Br(1) bond length. C(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Y(1)³⁺ and one C(1)²⁻ atom. The C(1)-C(1) bond length is 1.327 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms.

Y₂GeI₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Y₂GeI₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Y(1) is bonded to three equivalent Ge(1) and three equivalent I(1) atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing YGe₃I₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Y(1)-Ge(1) bond lengths are 2.892 Å. All Y(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.150 Å. Ge(1) is bonded to six equivalent Y(1) atoms to form edge-sharing GeY₆ octahedra. I(1) is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Y(1) atoms.

Al₂Si₄O₁₁ crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Al₂Si₄O₁₁ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to one O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2,3)²⁻ atoms to form AlO₅ trigonal bipyramids that share corners with four equivalent Si(1,2)O₄ tetrahedra;  a cornercorner with one Al(1)O₅ trigonal bipyramid; and edges with two equivalent Al(1)O₅ trigonal bipyramids. The Al(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.690 Å. There are two shorter (1.836 Å) and two longer (1.955 Å) Al(1)-O(2,3) bond lengths. Si(1,2)⁴⁺ is bonded to one O(2,3)²⁻; one O(6)²⁻; and two equivalent O(4,5)²⁻ atoms to form SiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Si(1,2)O₄ tetrahedra and corners with two equivalent Al(1)O₅ trigonal bipyramids. The Si(1,2)-O(2,3) bond length is 1.653 Å. The Si(1,2)-O(6) bond length is 1.623 Å. There is one shorter (1.634 Å) and one longer (1.635 Å) Si(1,2)-O(4,5) bond length. There are four inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2,3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Al(1)³⁺ and one Si(1,2)⁴⁺ atom. In the third O²⁻ site, O(4,5)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to two equivalent Si(1,2)⁴⁺ atoms. In the fourth O²⁻ site, O(6)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent Si(1,2)⁴⁺ atoms.

HgPSe₃ crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HgPSe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hg(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)²⁻, two equivalent Se(2)²⁻, and two equivalent Se(3)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.674 Å) and one longer (3.012 Å) Hg(1)-Se(1) bond length. There is one shorter (2.615 Å) and one longer (3.479 Å) Hg(1)-Se(2) bond length. There is one shorter (2.847 Å) and one longer (3.506 Å) Hg(1)-Se(3) bond length. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Se(1)²⁻, one Se(2)²⁻, and one Se(3)²⁻ atom. The P(1)-Se(1) bond length is 2.243 Å. The P(1)-Se(2) bond length is 2.233 Å. The P(1)-Se(3) bond length is 2.172 Å. There are three inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the third Se²⁻ site, Se(3)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

CaPbI₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CaPbI₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent I(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CaI₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Ca(1)I₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Pb(1)I₆ octahedra. Both Ca(1)-I(2) bond lengths are 3.141 Å. All Ca(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.142 Å. Pb(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent I(2)¹⁻ atoms to form PbI₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Pb(1)I₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Ca(1)I₆ octahedra. Both Pb(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.243 Å. All Pb(1)-I(2) bond lengths are 3.245 Å. There are two inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one Pb(1)²⁺ atom. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one Ca(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ atoms.

YBr₃ is Chromium trichloride-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YBr₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1,2)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing YBr₆ octahedra. All Y(1)-Br(1,2) bond lengths are 2.801 Å. Br(1,2)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms.

NdOI crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NdOI sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nd(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Nd(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.353 Å. All Nd(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.449 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Nd(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ONd₄ tetrahedra. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Nd(1)³⁺ atoms.

HoOBr crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HoOBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ho(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.269 Å) and three longer (2.272 Å) Ho(1)-O(1) bond lengths. All Ho(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.918 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ho(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OHo₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ho(1)³⁺ atoms.

ErOCl crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ErOCl sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Er(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing ErCl₂O₄ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 41°. There are two shorter (2.207 Å) and two longer (2.278 Å) Er(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Both Er(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.649 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Er(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OEr₄ tetrahedra. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Er(1)³⁺ atoms.

CrP₂S₇ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CrP₂S₇ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(1)²⁻, two equivalent S(2)²⁻, and two equivalent S(3)²⁻ atoms to form CrS₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra and edges with two equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra. Both Cr(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.401 Å. Both Cr(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.385 Å. Both Cr(1)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.358 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻, one S(2)²⁻, one S(3)²⁻, and one S(4)²⁻ atom to form PS₄ tetrahedra that share  a cornercorner with one Cr(1)S₆ octahedra,  a cornercorner with one P(1)S₄ tetrahedra, and  an edgeedge with one Cr(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 65°. The P(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.028 Å. The P(1)-S(2) bond length is 2.042 Å. The P(1)-S(3) bond length is 2.041 Å. The P(1)-S(4) bond length is 2.139 Å. There are four inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Cr(1)⁴⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one Cr(1)⁴⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the third S²⁻ site, S(3)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one Cr(1)⁴⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the fourth S²⁻ site, S(4)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent P(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

CoTeO₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CoTeO₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted CoO₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Co(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Co(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.198 Å. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.046 Å. Te(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form TeO₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Co(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Te(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.939 Å. All Te(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.047 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ and one Te(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Co(1)⁴⁺ and two equivalent Te(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

Sb crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Sb sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sb(1) is bonded in a hexagonal planar geometry to six equivalent Sb(1) atoms. All Sb(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.152 Å.

Ta₂Se crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two Ta₂Se sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent Ta sites. In the first Ta site, Ta(1) is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one Se(1) atom. The Ta(1)-Se(1) bond length is 2.882 Å. In the second Ta site, Ta(2) is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Se(1) atoms. All Ta(2)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.705 Å. Se(1) is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to one Ta(1) and four equivalent Ta(2) atoms.

As₂Se₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmn2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one As₂Se₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. As(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one Se(2)²⁻ and two equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. The As(1)-Se(2) bond length is 2.477 Å. There is one shorter (2.420 Å) and one longer (2.469 Å) As(1)-Se(1) bond length. There are two inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent As(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to two equivalent As(1)³⁺ atoms.

YTe₃ crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Te(1)¹⁻ and five equivalent Te(2)¹⁻ atoms. All Y(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.320 Å. There is one shorter (3.198 Å) and four longer (3.210 Å) Y(1)-Te(2) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Te¹⁻ sites. In the first Te¹⁻ site, Te(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Te¹⁻ site, Te(2)¹⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing TeY₅ trigonal bipyramids.

VBr₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one VBr₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. V(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing VBr₆ octahedra. All V(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.638 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent V(1)²⁺ atoms.

SiSb₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SiSb₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a hexagonal planar geometry to six equivalent Sb(1)+1.33- atoms. All Si(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.054 Å. Sb(1)+1.33- is bonded in a hexagonal planar geometry to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ and four equivalent Sb(1)+1.33- atoms. All Sb(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.054 Å.

SiAs₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmc2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SiAs₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent Si⁴⁺ sites. In the first Si⁴⁺ site, Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one As(1)²⁻, one As(2)²⁻, and two equivalent As(3)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiAs₄ tetrahedra. The Si(1)-As(1) bond length is 2.471 Å. The Si(1)-As(2) bond length is 2.411 Å. Both Si(1)-As(3) bond lengths are 2.412 Å. In the second Si⁴⁺ site, Si(2)⁴⁺ is bonded to one As(3)²⁻, one As(4)²⁻, and two equivalent As(2)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiAs₄ tetrahedra. The Si(2)-As(3) bond length is 2.396 Å. The Si(2)-As(4) bond length is 2.410 Å. Both Si(2)-As(2) bond lengths are 2.403 Å. There are four inequivalent As²⁻ sites. In the first As²⁻ site, As(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second As²⁻ site, As(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Si(1)⁴⁺ and two equivalent Si(2)⁴⁺ atoms. In the third As²⁻ site, As(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Si(2)⁴⁺ and two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the fourth As²⁻ site, As(4)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Si(2)⁴⁺ atom.

SiAs₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SiAs₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a hexagonal planar geometry to six equivalent As(1)+1.33- atoms. All Si(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.738 Å. As(1)+1.33- is bonded in a hexagonal planar geometry to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ and four equivalent As(1)+1.33- atoms. All As(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.738 Å.

WO₂ is Cyanogen Chloride-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of one WO₂ cluster. W(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both W(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.798 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one W(1)⁴⁺ atom.

TiS₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiS₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing TiS₆ octahedra. All Ti(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.428 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

TiO₂ is Cyanogen Chloride-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of one TiO₂ cluster. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Ti(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.718 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Ti(1)⁴⁺ atom.

SnO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SnO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sn(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing SnO₆ octahedra. All Sn(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.119 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Sn(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

CaClF crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CaClF sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ca(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.919 Å. All Ca(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.326 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FCa₄ tetrahedra.

K₂PdO₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmm space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of one K₂PdO₂ ribbon oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both K(1)-Pd(1) bond lengths are 2.882 Å. Both K(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.649 Å. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pd(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.074 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to two equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms.

CdBr₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CdBr₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CdBr₆ octahedra. All Cd(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.807 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ atoms.

CdBr₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CdBr₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CdBr₆ octahedra. All Cd(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.807 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ atoms.

SnS crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two SnS ribbons oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. Sn(1)²⁺ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Sn(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.603 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Sn(1)²⁺ atoms.

HfSe₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HfSe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hf(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)+1.33-, two equivalent Se(2)+1.33-, and four equivalent Se(3)+1.33- atoms. Both Hf(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.742 Å. Both Hf(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 2.742 Å. There are two shorter (2.721 Å) and two longer (2.889 Å) Hf(1)-Se(3) bond lengths. There are three inequivalent Se+1.33- sites. In the first Se+1.33- site, Se(1)+1.33- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Se+1.33- site, Se(2)+1.33- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the third Se+1.33- site, Se(3)+1.33- is bonded to four equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SeHf₄ trigonal pyramids.

P crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmna space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of two P clusters. P(1) is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one P(1) atom. The P(1)-P(1) bond length is 2.274 Å.

Nb₂O₅ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Nb₂O₅ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to one O(1)²⁻, one O(2)²⁻, and three equivalent O(3)²⁻ atoms. The Nb(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.734 Å. The Nb(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.939 Å. There are two shorter (2.044 Å) and one longer (2.172 Å) Nb(1)-O(3) bond length. There are three inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Nb(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

Ba₂N is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ba₂N sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ba(1) is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent N(1) atoms. All Ba(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.751 Å. N(1) is bonded to six equivalent Ba(1) atoms to form edge-sharing NBa₆ octahedra.

Ba₂ZrS₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ba₂ZrS₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 3.323 Å. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ and four equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing ZrS₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both Zr(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.606 Å. All Zr(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.459 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Zr(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing SBa₄Zr₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

NiP₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NiP₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ni(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent P(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ni(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.173 Å. P(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Ni(1)²⁺ and one P(1)¹⁻ atom. The P(1)-P(1) bond length is 2.097 Å.

AgNO₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmm2 space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of one AgNO₂ ribbon oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one N(1)³⁺ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. The Ag(1)-N(1) bond length is 2.133 Å. Both Ag(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.370 Å. N(1)³⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to one Ag(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both N(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.256 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one Ag(1)¹⁺ and one N(1)³⁺ atom.

Mg₂SiO₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Mg₂SiO₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. CNCl is Indium-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmm2 space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of one CNCl cluster. Ta₂PdSe₆ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ta₂PdSe₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Au₃SnP₇ crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Au₃SnP₇ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. The Sn(1)-P(2) bond length is 2.917 Å. The Sn(1)-P(3) bond length is 2.676 Å. The Sn(1)-P(6) bond length is 2.789 Å. There are seven inequivalent P+0.71- sites. The P(3)-P(7) bond length is 2.293 Å. In the fourth P+0.71- site, P(4)+0.71- is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Au(1)+0.33+, one P(2)+0.71-, and one P(5)+0.71- atom. In the fifth P+0.71- site, P(5)+0.71- is bonded to one Au(3)+0.33+, one P(1)+0.71-, one P(2)+0.71-, and one P(4)+0.71- atom to form distorted corner-sharing PP₃Au tetrahedra. K₂Se₅ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one K₂Se₅ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. Ta₃SeI₇ crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ta₃SeI₇ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb₃Br₈ crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Nb₃Br₈ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. PSi crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one PSi sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are three inequivalent Si⁴⁻ sites. Sr(AlCl₄)₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Sr(AlCl₄)₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. GaTeCl crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmn2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one GaTeCl sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. AlOCl crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AlOCl sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. W₂N is Molybdenite-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one W₂N sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. NbCl₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two NbCl₄ ribbons oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. RbMnP crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one RbMnP sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. AgO₂Cl crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pcca space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AgO₂Cl sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. AlCl₃ is Aluminum trichloride-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Nb₃SBr₇ crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Nb₃SBr₇ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)³⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻, one Br(3)¹⁻, two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻, and two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing NbSBr₅ octahedra. The Nb(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.422 Å. The Nb(1)-Br(3) bond length is 2.835 Å. Both Nb(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.582 Å. Both Nb(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 2.705 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ atoms. There are three inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ atoms. In the third Br¹⁻ site, Br(3)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ atoms.

Bi₂Se₂Te is trigonal omega-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Bi₂Se₂Te sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing BiTe₃Se₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Bi(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.268 Å. All Bi(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.892 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing TeBi₆ octahedra. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms.

TaPtTe₅ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TaPtTe₅ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻, two equivalent Te(2)²⁻, and four equivalent Te(3)²⁻ atoms. Both Ta(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.872 Å. Both Ta(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 2.965 Å. All Ta(1)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.895 Å. Pt(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Te(3)²⁻ and four equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing PtTe₆ octahedra. Both Pt(1)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.708 Å. All Pt(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 2.715 Å. There are three inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Ta(1)⁵⁺ and two equivalent Pt(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the third Te²⁻ site, Te(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ and one Pt(1)⁵⁺ atom.

KCN crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one KCN sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. There are a spread of K(1)-N(1) bond distances ranging from 2.776-3.109 Å. C(1)²⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one N(1)³⁻ atom. The C(1)-N(1) bond length is 1.176 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and one C(1)²⁺ atom.

Rb₃Mo₂Cl₉ crystallizes in the hexagonal P̅6m2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Rb₃Mo₂Cl₉ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent Rb¹⁺ sites. In the first Rb¹⁺ site, Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 3.521 Å. In the second Rb¹⁺ site, Rb(2)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ and six equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ atoms to form RbCl₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent Rb(2)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra and faces with six equivalent Mo(1)Cl₆ octahedra. All Rb(2)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 3.447 Å. All Rb(2)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 3.524 Å. Mo(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ and three equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ atoms to form MoCl₆ octahedra that share faces with three equivalent Rb(2)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra and  a faceface with one Mo(1)Cl₆ octahedra. All Mo(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.398 Å. All Mo(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 2.500 Å. There are two inequivalent Cl¹⁻ sites. In the first Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted L-shaped geometry to one Rb(2)¹⁺ and one Mo(1)³⁺ atom. In the second Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺, two equivalent Rb(2)¹⁺, and two equivalent Mo(1)³⁺ atoms.

CuInP₂Se₆ crystallizes in the trigonal P312 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CuInP₂Se₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form CuSe₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent In(1)Se₆ octahedra. All Cu(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.694 Å. In(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form InSe₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Cu(1)Se₆ octahedra. All In(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.808 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All P(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.222 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Cu(1)¹⁺, one In(1)¹⁺, and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

LuPS₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one LuPS₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Lu(1)³⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻, two equivalent S(2)²⁻, two equivalent S(3)²⁻, and two equivalent S(4)²⁻ atoms to form distorted LuS₇ pentagonal bipyramids that share  a cornercorner with one P(1)S₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Lu(1)S₇ pentagonal bipyramids, and edges with three equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra. The Lu(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.669 Å. There is one shorter (2.760 Å) and one longer (2.863 Å) Lu(1)-S(2) bond length. There is one shorter (2.763 Å) and one longer (2.783 Å) Lu(1)-S(3) bond length. There is one shorter (2.778 Å) and one longer (2.784 Å) Lu(1)-S(4) bond length. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻, one S(2)²⁻, one S(3)²⁻, and one S(4)²⁻ atom to form PS₄ tetrahedra that share  a cornercorner with one Lu(1)S₇ pentagonal bipyramid and edges with three equivalent Lu(1)S₇ pentagonal bipyramids. The P(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.008 Å. The P(1)-S(2) bond length is 2.085 Å. The P(1)-S(3) bond length is 2.074 Å. The P(1)-S(4) bond length is 2.068 Å. There are four inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one Lu(1)³⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Lu(1)³⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the third S²⁻ site, S(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Lu(1)³⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the fourth S²⁻ site, S(4)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Lu(1)³⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

NbCoTe₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmna space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NbCoTe₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms. Both Nb(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.867 Å. Both Nb(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 2.832 Å. Co(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms. Both Co(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.559 Å. There is one shorter (2.623 Å) and one longer (2.633 Å) Co(1)-Te(2) bond length. There are two inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Co(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Nb(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Co(1)²⁺ atoms.

As₂S₃ crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one As₂S₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are four inequivalent As³⁺ sites. In the first As³⁺ site, As(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one S(1)²⁻, one S(2)²⁻, and one S(3)²⁻ atom. The As(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.331 Å. The As(1)-S(2) bond length is 2.344 Å. The As(1)-S(3) bond length is 2.288 Å. In the second As³⁺ site, As(2)³⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one S(1)²⁻, one S(4)²⁻, and one S(5)²⁻ atom. The As(2)-S(1) bond length is 2.317 Å. The As(2)-S(4) bond length is 2.279 Å. The As(2)-S(5) bond length is 2.314 Å. In the third As³⁺ site, As(3)³⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one S(2)²⁻, one S(3)²⁻, and one S(6)²⁻ atom. The As(3)-S(2) bond length is 2.277 Å. The As(3)-S(3) bond length is 2.338 Å. The As(3)-S(6) bond length is 2.331 Å. In the fourth As³⁺ site, As(4)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one S(4)²⁻, one S(5)²⁻, and one S(6)²⁻ atom. The As(4)-S(4) bond length is 2.332 Å. The As(4)-S(5) bond length is 2.276 Å. The As(4)-S(6) bond length is 2.320 Å. There are six inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one As(1)³⁺ and one As(2)³⁺ atom. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one As(1)³⁺ and one As(3)³⁺ atom. In the third S²⁻ site, S(3)²⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one As(1)³⁺ and one As(3)³⁺ atom. In the fourth S²⁻ site, S(4)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to one As(2)³⁺ and one As(4)³⁺ atom. In the fifth S²⁻ site, S(5)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to one As(2)³⁺ and one As(4)³⁺ atom. In the sixth S²⁻ site, S(6)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to one As(3)³⁺ and one As(4)³⁺ atom.

Ta₂PdS₆ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ta₂PdS₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(2)²⁻, two equivalent S(3)²⁻, and three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing TaS₇ pentagonal bipyramids. Both Ta(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.504 Å. Both Ta(1)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.495 Å. There are two shorter (2.499 Å) and one longer (2.627 Å) Ta(1)-S(1) bond length. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to two equivalent S(2)²⁻ and two equivalent S(3)²⁻ atoms. Both Pd(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.356 Å. Both Pd(1)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.355 Å. There are three inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ and one Pd(1)²⁺ atom. In the third S²⁻ site, S(3)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ and one Pd(1)²⁺ atom.

PdI₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one PdI₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent I(2)¹⁻ and three equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing PdI₅ square pyramids. There is one shorter (2.646 Å) and one longer (2.656 Å) Pd(1)-I(2) bond length. There are a spread of Pd(1)-I(1) bond distances ranging from 2.637-3.265 Å. There are two inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms.

HoSI crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HoSI sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ho(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ and two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing HoS₄I₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 20°. There are two shorter (2.695 Å) and two longer (2.728 Å) Ho(1)-S(1) bond lengths. Both Ho(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.023 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ho(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SHo₄ trigonal pyramids. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ho(1)³⁺ atoms.

SiS is alpha Selenium-derived structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmna space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of two SiS ribbons oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. Si(1)²⁺ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Si(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.170 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Si(1)²⁺ atoms.

TbGaI crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TbGaI sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Tb(1) is bonded to six equivalent Ga(1) and three equivalent I(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing TbGa₆I₃ octahedra. There are three shorter (2.931 Å) and three longer (3.386 Å) Tb(1)-Ga(1) bond lengths. All Tb(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.141 Å. Ga(1) is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Tb(1) and three equivalent Ga(1) atoms. All Ga(1)-Ga(1) bond lengths are 2.519 Å. I(1) is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Tb(1) atoms.

FeAl₂S₄ crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one FeAl₂S₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Fe(1)²⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(4)²⁻ atoms to form FeS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Al(1)S₆ octahedra and corners with six equivalent Fe(1)S₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 60°. The Fe(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.384 Å. All Fe(1)-S(4) bond lengths are 2.221 Å. There are two inequivalent Al³⁺ sites. In the first Al³⁺ site, Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form AlS₆ octahedra that share corners with three equivalent Fe(1)S₄ tetrahedra, corners with three equivalent Al(2)S₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Al(1)S₆ octahedra. All Al(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.376 Å. All Al(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.516 Å. In the second Al³⁺ site, Al(2)³⁺ is bonded to one S(2)²⁻ and three equivalent S(3)²⁻ atoms to form AlS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Al(1)S₆ octahedra and corners with six equivalent Al(2)S₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 55°. The Al(2)-S(2) bond length is 2.213 Å. All Al(2)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.290 Å. There are four inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Fe(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form distorted corner-sharing SAl₃Fe tetrahedra. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to one Al(2)³⁺ and three equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms. In the third S²⁻ site, S(3)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Al(2)³⁺ atoms. In the fourth S²⁻ site, S(4)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Fe(1)²⁺ atoms.

CoNb₂S₄ is beta indium sulfide-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CoNb₂S₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)+3.50+ is bonded in a rectangular see-saw-like geometry to one S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms. The Nb(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.429 Å. All Nb(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.438 Å. Co(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoS₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.268 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Nb(1)+3.50+ and three equivalent Co(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SNbCo₃ trigonal pyramids. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)+3.50+ atoms.

HfTe₃ is I4/mcm-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HfTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hf(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(1)+1.33-, two equivalent Te(3)+1.33-, and four equivalent Te(2)+1.33- atoms. Both Hf(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.950 Å. Both Hf(1)-Te(3) bond lengths are 2.950 Å. There are two shorter (2.957 Å) and two longer (3.204 Å) Hf(1)-Te(2) bond lengths. There are three inequivalent Te+1.33- sites. In the first Te+1.33- site, Te(1)+1.33- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second Te+1.33- site, Te(2)+1.33- is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the third Te+1.33- site, Te(3)+1.33- is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

LuTe₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one LuTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Lu(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to one Te(1)¹⁻ and six equivalent Te(2)¹⁻ atoms. The Lu(1)-Te(1) bond length is 3.117 Å. There are four shorter (3.035 Å) and two longer (3.457 Å) Lu(1)-Te(2) bond lengths. There are three inequivalent Te¹⁻ sites. In the first Te¹⁻ site, Te(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Lu(1)³⁺ and four equivalent Te(3)¹⁻ atoms. All Te(1)-Te(3) bond lengths are 3.105 Å. In the second Te¹⁻ site, Te(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Lu(1)³⁺ and one Te(3)¹⁻ atom. The Te(2)-Te(3) bond length is 3.708 Å. In the third Te¹⁻ site, Te(3)¹⁻ is bonded to one Te(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent Te(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing TeTe₅ square pyramids.

DyTe₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmma space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one DyTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Dy(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to one Te(1)¹⁻ and six equivalent Te(2)¹⁻ atoms. The Dy(1)-Te(1) bond length is 3.162 Å. ThTe₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ThTe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Th(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Te(1)+1.33-, two equivalent Te(3)+1.33-, and four equivalent Te(2)+1.33- atoms. Both Th(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.210 Å. Ag₃SnP₇ crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ag₃SnP₇ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are three inequivalent Ag¹⁺ sites. In the first Ag¹⁺ site, Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one P(4)+0.71-, one P(5)+0.71-, and two equivalent P(1)+0.71- atoms. The Ag(1)-P(4) bond length is 2.615 Å. The Ag(1)-P(5) bond length is 2.519 Å. There is one shorter (2.639 Å) and one longer (2.721 Å) Ag(1)-P(1) bond length. In the second Ag¹⁺ site, Ag(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ag(3)¹⁺, one P(6)+0.71-, and one P(7)+0.71- atom. There is one shorter (3.078 Å) and one longer (3.159 Å) Ag(2)-Ag(3) bond length. The Ag(2)-P(6) bond length is 2.487 Å. The Ag(2)-P(7) bond length is 2.451 Å. In the third Ag¹⁺ site, Ag(3)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ag(2)¹⁺, one P(1)+0.71-, one P(2)+0.71-, and one P(3)+0.71- atom. The Ag(3)-P(1) bond length is 2.752 Å. The Ag(3)-P(2) bond length is 2.431 Å. The Ag(3)-P(3) bond length is 2.432 Å. Sn(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one P(1)+0.71-, one P(3)+0.71-, one P(5)+0.71-, and one P(7)+0.71- atom. In the first P+0.71- site, P(1)+0.71- is bonded in a distorted pentagonal planar geometry to one Ag(3)¹⁺, two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺, one Sn(1)²⁺, and one P(4)+0.71- atom. The P(1)-P(4) bond length is 2.143 Å. In the second P+0.71- site, P(2)+0.71- is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one Ag(3)¹⁺, one P(3)+0.71-, one P(6)+0.71-, and one P(7)+0.71- atom. The P(2)-P(3) bond length is 2.275 Å. The P(2)-P(6) bond length is 2.273 Å. The P(2)-P(7) bond length is 2.237 Å. HgI₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal P̅4m2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HgI₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded to one I(2)¹⁻, one I(3)¹⁻, and two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing HgI₄ tetrahedra. The Hg(1)-I(2) bond length is 2.869 Å. The Hg(1)-I(3) bond length is 2.848 Å. Both Hg(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.843 Å. There are three inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms. In the third I¹⁻ site, I(3)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms.

Lix₀CoO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoO₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.876 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ atoms.
